sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM design_parameters
WHERE set_by = 1 AND parameter_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Gardener" refers to the user with ID 1;
- "Seeds" metaphorically represent the files uploaded by the user;
- "Digital garden" represents the `design_files` table.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(file_id) AS number_of_files
FROM design_files
WHERE uploaded_by = 1;

external_knowledge:
- A "device family" refers to a group of devices that share similar characteristics or belong to the same product line;
- "Design projects" are unique projects associated with a device, often involving the configuration or customization of the device;
- "Total power consumption" is the sum of the maximum power consumption values for all devices within a family that have associated design projects.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(parameter_id) AS parameter_count
FROM version_parameters
WHERE version_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Gardeners" refer to users in the system;
- "Plots" refer to design projects;
- "Seeds" refer to comments;
- "Tools" refer to devices;
- "Cultivated" refers to the creation of design projects;
- "Used" refers to the creation of versions.

- 'C_FAMILY' refers to the family of the device, which can include families like Spartan or Virtex;
- 'power_consumption' is a metric that measures the maximum power consumption of the device;
- 'completed' status indicates that the design project is finished and finalized.

- "Latest versions" refers to the versions with the most recent creation dates for each design project;
- "Performance metrics" include reports on area, speed, power, and other relevant metrics;
- "Device details" include the device name, manufacturer, family, model, pin count, package type, power consumption, and clock frequency.

- 'Complex' design projects are those that are considered to have a high level of complexity;
- 'Completed' design projects are those that have been finalized and are not in progress;
- 'Xilinx' is a well-known manufacturer of FPGA devices;
- 'Virtex' is a family of high-performance FPGA devices by Xilinx.

- 'Speed' in this context refers to the performance metric of the device, specifically how fast it can operate;
- 'The day when the technological harvest was reaped' refers to the report date '2022-01-15';
- 'Seeds of innovation sown by Xilinx in the Virtex family' refers to devices manufactured by Xilinx and belonging to the Virtex family.

sql:
SELECT family, AVG(power_consumption) AS average_power_consumption
FROM devices
GROUP BY family;

external_knowledge:
- "recently updated" refers to designs modified within the specified date range (January 1, 2022, to January 31, 2022);
- "power parameters" are parameters in the category 'power';
- "at least one report" means the design has one or more reports.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS comment_count
FROM design_comments
WHERE design_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_searches, search_type
FROM search_history
GROUP BY search_type;

SELECT COUNT(comment_id) AS comment_count
FROM design_comments
WHERE design_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Fully blossomed' refers to projects with a status of 'completed';
- 'Intricate flowers' refers to projects with a complexity level of 'complex';
- 'Parameter settings' include the parameter names, values, and data types;
- 'Aggregated performance metrics' include the total area, total speed, and total power.

- 'bloomed in the last year' refers to designs created within the last year;
- 'reached maturity' refers to designs that are in the 'completed' status;
- 'crafted by the wizard Xilinx' refers to designs associated with devices manufactured by Xilinx.

sql:
SELECT manufacturer, SUM(power_consumption) AS total_power_consumption
FROM devices
GROUP BY manufacturer;

SELECT d.device_name, des.design_name, des.description
FROM designs des
INNER JOIN devices d ON des.device_id = d.device_id;

SELECT user_id, COUNT(design_id) AS designs_count
FROM designs
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'blossoms' refers to design projects;
- 'nutrients' refers to parameters set for the designs;
- 'gardeners' refers to users who set the parameters;
- 'tended to them' means the parameters were set by the users;
- The query helps in tracking the parameters and their values, set dates, and the users responsible for setting them, providing a clear view of the design projects' configurations.

- 'Completed and released' refers to design projects that are marked as 'completed' and have versions that are marked as 'released';
- 'Total area value' is the sum of the metric values for the metric named 'area';
- 'User activity' is measured by the number of user sessions where the session end time is not null.
